Vanderbilt Gold Corp saidshareholders at a special meeting approved its reincorporationin Delaware, an increase in authorized common to 25 mln sharesfrom 12 mln shares, and a non-qualified stock option plan.    It also said shareholders approved the merger of MorningStar Mine interests held by six corporations in exchange forissuing 2,098,602 shares of its common. It said the acquisitionbrings its ownership in Morning to over 94 pct and it intendsto acquire the remaining interests before mid year.    It said its plans call for 1987 production of 30,000 ouncesof gold with product costs per ounce at about 200 dlrs. Reuter&#3;